    dc:creator "Tea, Yi-Kai; Frable, Benjamin W.; Wal, Cara Van Der" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "Redescription and phylogenetic placement of Cirrhilabrus sanguineus Cornic (Teleostei: Labridae), with first documentation of the female form" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611710>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611716>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611722>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611705>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611714>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611720>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611725>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611718>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611707>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611727> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611710>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, male, approximately 90 mm TL, from Cannoniers Point, off the northern coast of Mauritius. Specimen not retained. Note asymmetry of magenta blotch on A: left facing side and B: right facing side. Photo by S. K. Tea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611710/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611716>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, male in nuptial display, approximately 70 mm TL, from Flic en Flac, off the western coast of Mauritius. Note the prominent stripes along the upper and lower edges of the orbit. Specimen not retained. Photo by H. Tanaka." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Map of Mauritius in the western Indian Ocean showing distribution records of Cirrhilabrus sanguineus (closed circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611705>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, freshly preserved male neotype, BPBM 24779, 66.5 mm SL, from Flic en Flac, off the western coast of Mauritius (top). Photo by J.E. Randall. Current neotype in preservation (below). Note broken rays in the dorsal, caudal, and anal fins. Photo by B.W. Frable." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611705/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611714>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, x-radiograph of BPBM 24779, 66.5 mm SL, neotype (above), and BPBM 22542, 48.3 mm SL (below). Radiograph by B.W. Frable." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611714/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611720>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, freshly euthanized female, ZRC 60168, 41.2 mm SL, from Cannoniers Point, off the northern coast of Mauritius. DNA sample obtained from right pectoral fin. Photo by K. Lim." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611720/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611725>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Bayesian phylogeny of selected Cirrhilabrus species inferred using the mitochondrial CO1 marker. Paracheilinus angulatus was used as the outgroup. Support values at nodes correspond to posterior probability and likelihood bootstrap percentages. Dagger (†) represent new, de novo sequences generated and used in this study; Filled circles represent species with strongly lanceolate caudal fins (black) and weakly lanceolate caudal fins (grey); Members of the Cirrhilabrus jordani complex from the western Pacific Ocean are coloured blue, while those from the western Indian Ocean are coloured green." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611725/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611718>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, female, approximately 45 mm TL, from Cannoniers Point, off the northern coast of Mauritius. Image reversed, specimen not retained. Photo by S.K. Tea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611718/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611707>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cirrhilabrus sanguineus, male, approximately 80 mm TL, from Cannoniers Point, off the northern coast of Mauritius. Image reversed, specimen not retained. Photo by S.K. Tea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611707/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2611727>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Preserved specimens of Cirrhilabrus blatteus. Note the unique purple staining in several of its ossified elements (interorbitals, maxilla and operculum), scales and fin rays. Photo by Y.K. Tea, photographed at the California Academy of Sciences." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2611727/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

